"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-ruthless-and-hungrier-mindset-needed-for-team-singapore-as-paris-olympics-beckons\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  Sport Singapore chief executive Alan Goh (centre) and Singapore Sport Institute chief Su Chun Wei (left) on ST's Hard Tackle podcast.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.932442455090965e-18, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 293, \"end\": 302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 333, \"end\": 336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\", \"score\": 0.9995944179541124, \"rank\": 0.00036400790803651736, \"text\": \"Wei\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: ST PODCASTS  Deepanraj Ganesan  PublishedJan 24, 2024, 05:58 PM  UpdatedNov 08, 2024, 01:52 PM  SINGAPORE -As Singapore sports head into a new year with the Olympics on the horizon, Sport Singapore (SportSG) chief executive Alan Goh wants local athletes to be \\\"ruthless\\\" and \\\"hungrier\\\" in their pursuit of success.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 491, \"end\": 500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 563, \"end\": 578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Singapore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sport Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Singapore\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a wide-ranging interview on The Straits Times' Hard Tackle podcast published on Jan 24, Goh, who was alongside Singapore Sport Institute (SSI) chief Su Chun Wei, said the Republic must build on last October's Asian Games in Hangzhou where Singapore's athletes claimed three gold, six silver and seven bronze medals.\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 1015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Straits_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Straits Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Straits_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Straits_Times\"}, {\"begin\": 811, \"end\": 820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 857, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\", \"score\": 0.9995944179541124, \"rank\": 0.00036400790803651736, \"text\": \"Wei\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\"}, {\"begin\": 909, \"end\": 914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.297787979446252e-20, \"text\": \"Asian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 924, \"end\": 932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.934226022683058e-18, \"text\": \"Hangzhou\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\"}, {\"begin\": 939, \"end\": 948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite that tally being the country's worst-ever haul of golds and overall medals this millennium, Su at the post-Games conference had hailed the outing as a successful one with \\\"significant wins\\\" for the contingent.\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked during the podcast whether there is a need to be more ruthless in their assessment, Goh said: \\\"We do not want to just be comfortable with that performance in Hangzhou.\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1400, \"end\": 1408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.934226022683058e-18, \"text\": \"Hangzhou\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But we say successful contextually because we see the trajectory and potential of where we can go.\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But yes, I agree with you, we should be ruthless about it.\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We should not be satisfied.\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's not the attitude and posture we want Team Singapore to have coming out of Hangzhou, we want them to be hungrier.\\\"\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1651, \"end\": 1660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 1683, \"end\": 1691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.934226022683058e-18, \"text\": \"Hangzhou\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He highlighted how swimmer Letitia Sim, 20, exemplified that ruthless approach.\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sim missed out on an Asiad medal three times in China but managed to pick herself up.\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asiad\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1852, \"end\": 1857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9102537831798161, \"rank\": 0.09858645860511892, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Japan Open in November, she became Singapore's first female swimmer to meet the qualifying time for the Paris Olympics in the 100m breaststroke while also setting a new national record.\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 2083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1933, \"end\": 1942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Su maintained that it had been a successful Asiad while urging athletes and coaches to \\\"learn from the experience\\\" and \\\"be ruthless about getting the medal\\\".\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2129, \"end\": 2134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asiad\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among Singapore's standout stars for the July 26-Aug 11 Olympics are sprint queen Shanti Pereira and kitefoiling world champion Maximilian Maeder.\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2390, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2250, \"end\": 2259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 2326, \"end\": 2340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shanti_Pereira\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shanti Pereira\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shanti_Pereira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shanti_Pereira\"}, {\"begin\": 2372, \"end\": 2382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maximilian_I_of_Mexico\", \"score\": 0.9999987904446282, \"rank\": 1.1202495041302981e-06, \"text\": \"Maximilian\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maximilian_I_of_Mexico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maximilian_I_of_Mexico\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Goh described the latter, who is only 17, as \\\"very intelligent, very mature and level-headed\\\", and said the young sailor is being supported by SSI and SportSG even as he trains abroad.\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2576, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He added: \\\"Because of the nature of sailing, his best training areas are not in Singapore.\", \"from\": 2578, \"to\": 2668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2658, \"end\": 2667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So SSI and SportSG have to make sure that wherever he is, we give him the best support.\", \"from\": 2669, \"to\": 2756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do have direct conversations with him, his parents, and there is a two-way feedback between his family and us.\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2871, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The key is to keep him focused on Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 2872, \"to\": 2917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2906, \"end\": 2916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.97828942158753e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have fingers crossed.\", \"from\": 2919, \"to\": 2944, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the world champion but at same time, we do not put undue pressure on him.\", \"from\": 2945, \"to\": 3024, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But we are quietly confident that he will stay focused and fly our flag high in Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3112, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3105, \"end\": 3110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995793587, \"rank\": 4.2063130597309434e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Singapore Sport Institute chief Su Chun Wei (left) and Sport Singapore chief executive Alan Goh on ST's Hard Tackle podcast.\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3114, \"end\": 3123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 3154, \"end\": 3157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\", \"score\": 0.9995944179541124, \"rank\": 0.00036400790803651736, \"text\": \"Wei\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Wei\"}, {\"begin\": 3169, \"end\": 3184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Singapore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sport Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Singapore\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: ST PODCASTS  As for Pereira, 27, Su is eager to see her get even quicker and said she is on \\\"an exciting journey\\\".\", \"from\": 3240, \"to\": 3361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3267, \"end\": 3274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Pereira\", \"score\": 0.9999996597026108, \"rank\": 3.40297352247782e-07, \"text\": \"Pereira\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Pereira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Pereira\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2023, she bagged the 100m-200m double at the SEA Games and Asian championships, before adding the 200m gold in Hangzhou.\", \"from\": 3363, \"to\": 3486, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3425, \"end\": 3430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.297787979446252e-20, \"text\": \"Asian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 3477, \"end\": 3485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.934226022683058e-18, \"text\": \"Hangzhou\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also reached the 200m semi-finals of the world championships, which earned her a spot at Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 3488, \"to\": 3592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was her first qualification on merit for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3650, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Su said: \\\"She is only beginning to discover where we can break through and she is quietly working together with Luis (Cunha), with the team who continue to prime her in good shape.\", \"from\": 3652, \"to\": 3832, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Let us watch this space, let us cheer her on and get excited.\\\"\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 3897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team Singapore had won medals from the 2008 to 2016 Olympics, but returned home empty-handed from the Tokyo Games in 2021.\", \"from\": 3899, \"to\": 4021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beyond individual athletic performances, Goh also highlighted an active sporting calendar in 2024.\", \"from\": 4023, \"to\": 4121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Singapore will host table tennis' Singapore Smash in March, the Professional Triathletes Organisation Asian Open in April and World Rugby HSBC SVNS in May.\", \"from\": 4122, \"to\": 4277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4122, \"end\": 4131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 4224, \"end\": 4234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Open_Figure_Skating_Trophy\", \"score\": 0.9854478647724051, \"rank\": 0.014767026997479532, \"text\": \"Asian Open\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Open_Figure_Skating_Trophy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Open_Figure_Skating_Trophy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More events are expected to be added later in the year.\", \"from\": 4278, \"to\": 4333, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is important to strike a balance between events for spectators and those that Singaporeans can excel and be competitive in, Goh said.\", \"from\": 4335, \"to\": 4471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4416, \"end\": 4428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singaporeans\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.835714403873263e-13, \"text\": \"Singaporeans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singaporeans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singaporeans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He noted: \\\"I will be candid to say that when you bring in events that are too high-level, they are actually more for the spectators.\", \"from\": 4473, \"to\": 4605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We need the very high-end because we all celebrate sports and are fans, but we also want those that Singapore athletes can take part in and benefit from the experience and do well.\\\"\", \"from\": 4606, \"to\": 4787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4706, \"end\": 4715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport Singapore  Singapore sports  Sports and recreation  Olympics 2024  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 4789, \"to\": 4977, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4806, \"end\": 4815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999979399945, \"rank\": 2.059979553418517e-09, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 4894, \"end\": 4902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 4978, \"to\": 4992, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 4994, \"to\": 5011, \"entities\": []}]}"